<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-80619D2B-B0E6-4881-A840-5775E79E913C" version="3" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-80619D2B-B0E6-4881-A840-5775E79E913C" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">Random dots/stripes</title><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Diagnostics</category><category class="- topic/category ">Diagnostics</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><section id="GUID-50B00AD6-0A38-41AB-B3CF-DCE2951AFA8A" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "/><table id="GUID-53E5F599-B620-44AD-919D-C7253ABD770C" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Schematic overview 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Real example 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-24E04507-5DBB-43EE-BC3C-00F800301EC9" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-D35D03A2-0D6D-4E10-8F34-522B8B0339E7-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-D35D03A2-0D6D-4E10-8F34-522B8B0339E7-low.png"/></fig><fig id="GUID-68D4BEC3-D507-4911-964F-B34C8156773A" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-6CC18FCC-46AF-4AB1-B154-47B0E1A634B5-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-6CC18FCC-46AF-4AB1-B154-47B0E1A634B5-low.png"/></fig></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-73A4DA69-010A-4414-A4DB-E1E481E37FE8" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-FAF9625F-0E28-4E0A-BD61-F62ECB707B3D-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-FAF9625F-0E28-4E0A-BD61-F62ECB707B3D-low.png"/></fig><fig id="GUID-DE002F73-7622-46BB-B57B-7D9A66389807" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-E1EA9D07-1BB8-4EAE-86DA-167412A98D05-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-E1EA9D07-1BB8-4EAE-86DA-167412A98D05-low.png"/></fig></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-EC1EAE23-40EC-4B10-A2C9-83873F76DC70" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Collect</title><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Symptoms</b> 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Random located dots/stripes in carriage (Y)-direction. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> In most cases related to mediastep size 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">All colors possible 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Dots/Stripes are on top of the ink layer 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Sometimes ink pollution is also visible outside the media width (platen or maintenance unit) 
</p></li></ul></section><section id="GUID-07C8D19A-B969-41D0-A879-C84A1CA58BA6" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Functional Logging (if available)</title><p class="- topic/p "> 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> 
<i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i "> Printhead score</i> 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> One of the causes of darker spots can be a loose nozzle plate (C1640/C1650). A sudden "sharp" decrease in printhead score might indicate an event which caused a loose nozzle plate (See example below). 
</p><fig id="GUID-A3292D9E-2C40-4811-B0AD-FAB41795DA06" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-23C48FE0-23D0-4471-A091-CA2BB6631121-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-23C48FE0-23D0-4471-A091-CA2BB6631121-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p "> In most cases this is also accompanied by an ADAM trigger (see below). 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">However in case of pollution of the matrix-plate or carriage no deviations are seen in printhead performance. 
</p></section><section id="GUID-B7B43247-F1BE-4779-8619-AE5A550AF2F8" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">ADAM-triggers</title><p class="- topic/p ">In some cases 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">04-T-001</b> is given in ADAM. In those cases replace the mentioned printhead as this is most likely this cause of the ink pollution. 
</p></section><section id="GUID-DDCC1BB0-B402-4010-9156-67DB737F3DE5" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Analyze/Repair</title><fig id="GUID-17DF3B73-8BA4-4953-9843-B9C96569627F" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-79D66F07-DD0B-4477-B1CC-2D5095211118-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-79D66F07-DD0B-4477-B1CC-2D5095211118-svg.svg"/></fig></section><section id="GUID-BB9BDDD1-E29C-42C5-BF10-2854E3AE4223" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Steps explanation</title><table pgwide="1" id="GUID-D963269B-E108-446A-A212-4581FEAA8740" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="4" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="20*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col4" colnum="4" colwidth="30*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Type 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">To do 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Decision 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Check if the matrix plate and bottom of printhead carriage are clean 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Focus also on small fibers attached to the matrix plate or bottom of the printhead carriage 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Clean the matrix plate and bottom of the printhead carriage and check on media fibers 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><xref href="http://localhost:20346/VIDEO10004EN.US/video05/index.html" format="html" scope="external" class="- topic/xref "><?ditaot usertext?>Clean the Matrix Plate</xref> 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Clean the bottom of the printhead carriage (eg: mirrors, M&amp;C-scanner,..) 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Decision 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Check if the platen is polluted. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-49E70A38-260E-4950-B239-C1606E8F15D4" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-88F1A489-8807-4EF9-BA3A-81436E7B4578-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-88F1A489-8807-4EF9-BA3A-81436E7B4578-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Clean the platen 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><xref href="http://localhost:20346/VIDEO10004EN.US/video06/index.html" format="html" scope="external" class="- topic/xref "><?ditaot usertext?>Clean the Platen 
</xref> 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">5 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Decision 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Check if the ink tubes on the backside of the printhead carriage are leaking 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-A592072E-F13D-4395-A6F0-764988923780" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-E40A04A1-50A8-4411-83FD-EC2AFEF3B29C-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-E40A04A1-50A8-4411-83FD-EC2AFEF3B29C-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">6 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Reconnect valves 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">7 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Decision 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Check whether 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">04-T-001</b> is present in ADAM 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">8 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Replace the affected printheads 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><xref keyref="04DISA002" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-75F1003D-F727-49BD-88A7-1CEF7223F097.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 04 How to replace a (failing) printhead: Overview document?>04 How to replace a (failing) printhead: Overview document</xref> 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">9 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Decision 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Check if warning 79xx or error 75xx are present. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">10 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Identify the leakage 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><xref keyref="07DIAGIDENTIFYLEAKAGE001" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-D8F4A0EA-5E9A-4C9A-8EC6-8982C873948E.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 07 How to identify a leakage of the pressure system?>07 How to identify a leakage of the pressure system</xref> 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">11 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Perform SDS 07-6-009 to check the performance of the maintenance unit 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-2513E5DF-C282-453D-9841-6E539DB0EB51" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Evaluate/Prevention</title><p class="- topic/p ">As Media with a high content of fibers (eg. Textile) can release these fibers additional attention is required for regular maintenance (see examples below). 
</p><fig id="GUID-8A88A28D-44E5-432D-BC3D-60EF712102A2" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-59ECF9C8-9244-472F-ACF2-6132CFEDAB4B-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-59ECF9C8-9244-472F-ACF2-6132CFEDAB4B-low.png"/></fig><fig id="GUID-C311ADCC-BBBB-460F-A392-8BF5207B3C71" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-93CD7A14-991F-4A06-A537-6B39A60D96F0-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-93CD7A14-991F-4A06-A537-6B39A60D96F0-low.png"/></fig></section><section id="GUID-987F83F9-80F0-41BC-B82B-BB16DA268203" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Background info</title><p class="- topic/p "> When the matrix plate or printhead carriage is polluted by a large amount of ink, this ink can fall down on the print surface. This will create an random pattern in the carriage direction. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> In most cases this ink pollution can be removed by performing the manual maintenance procedure of the matrix plate. Also large fibers from the media on the matrix plate can cause additional pollution of ink. These can also be cleaned by the manual maintenance procedure. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> In case printheads or maintenance unit are damaged the ink pollution will reappear within a few prints. 
</p></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-BDE42A10-0DAA-46D3-99F7-D18695E3843E.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Solutions</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
</task>